      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Tracing for medium of performance term <em>see also from</em> reference.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <p>Used in an established term record to trace a <em>&gt;see also from</em> reference from an
               		    established medium of performance term to a related established term.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <div>
            <p>Most of the content designators defined for field 562 are the same as those defined for
               				field 162 (Heading-Medium of Performance Term), field 462 (See From Tracing-Medium of 
               				Performance Term), and field 762 (Subdivision Heading Linking Entry-Medium of Performance Term).
               				Description, guidelines, and input conventions for shared content designators are given in
               				the <em><a href="adx62.html">X62 Medium of Performance Term-General Information</a></em> section.
            </p>
            <p>Guidelines for applying the subfield $w (Control subfield),
				subfield $i (Relationship information) and subfield $4 (Relationship code) in
				field 562 are given in the <em><a href="adtracing.html">Tracings and References-General Information</a></em> section.
            </p>
         </div>
